column6: Appears much too low compared with peak on the Hogsmill and Wandle.
Peak from wrack marks. Flow estimates from 24 to 34m3/s, depending on backwater effects.

Recorder out of commission from 2 to 25 August 1981. Archive originally 7.07m3/s, later amended to 17.07m3/s. Black&Veatch suggested around 20m3/s, based on extent of flooding, which was probably more than in 1960.
